Statistical Business Analysis Report
________________________________________
1. Introduction
In today’s data-driven business environment, statistical analysis plays a crucial role in understanding performance patterns and supporting strategic decision-making. This project focuses on applying statistical techniques to analyze business sales data and evaluate the impact of marketing expenditure on revenue generation.
The primary objective of this study is to:
•	Analyze sales performance using descriptive statistics
•	Test business assumptions through hypothesis testing
•	Examine relationships between marketing spend and sales
•	Build a regression model to quantify marketing effectiveness
•	Translate statistical findings into actionable business insights
This report demonstrates how statistical methods such as hypothesis testing, correlation analysis, confidence intervals, and regression analysis can be used to support business decisions.
________________________________________
2. Dataset Description
The dataset used in this analysis represents simulated business sales data collected over multiple months and regions. It reflects realistic business operations and marketing investments.
Dataset Variables
Column Name	Description
Month	Month of sales activity
Region	Business region (A, B, C)
Marketing_Spend	Total marketing expenditure
Online_Ads	Online advertising spend
Store_Promotions	In-store promotion cost
Sales	Total sales revenue
Dataset Characteristics
•	Number of records: 50+ observations
•	Data type: Numerical and categorical
•	No missing values
•	Suitable for statistical testing and regression modeling
This dataset enables analysis of both temporal trends and regional performance, making it ideal for business-oriented statistical analysis.
